s.usage_not_supported_checkout_session":"{paymentMethod} doesn’t support Checkout Sessions in <code>setup</code> mode.","easel.elements_inspector.filtering_messages.usage_not_supported_intent":"{paymentMethod} doesn’t support <code>usage=off_session</code> for SetupIntents.","easel.elements_inspector.filtering_messages.wallet_disallowed_from_options":"This wallet is disabled in the wallets config in your Payment Element options.","easel.inbox.create_google_maps_api_key":"Create a Google Maps API key","easel.inbox.dashboard_payment_methods":"Update your payment method preferences","easel.inbox.heading.error":"Error","easel.inbox.heading.warning":"Warning","easel.inbox.heading.info":"Optimization","easel.inbox.heading.success":"Success","easel.inbox.message.stripe_js_initialization_deferred":"The Stripe.js SDK is required to render the Payment Element and securely collect payment details. For optimal latency, load the script and initialize the Stripe.js constructor early in the user’s session to prevent the script from blocking rendering.","easel.inbox.message.multiple_stripe_js_instances":"Creating multiple instances of the Stripe.js constructor within a single user session can hinder the performance of the Payment Element and your site. If using the same publishable key, create and share a single instance with a singleton pattern. In single-page applications, it is safe and recommended to share the Stripe.js instance across pages.","easel.inbox.message.multiple_elements_instances":"A Payment Element integration uses an Elements instance to manage a group of elements. When using the Payment Element with other elements—such as the Address Element or Express Checkout Element—create all elements within the same Elements instance for optimal performance.","easel.inbox.message.checkout_session_pricing_usage":"Use the amount and currency provided by your Checkout Session when displaying total and line-item prices. This will ensure consistency and proper localization.","eas